{
  "texts": [
    "The second system then develops a semantic graph by turning dense region captions into textual scene graphs (using SPICE), as well as a knowledge graph generated using the question input.",
    "A message passing GNN is then used to identify the important nodes and aggregate information between them using an attention weighting.",
    "A joint representation for each knowledge graph node is then learned by combining the whole semantic graph with the node with relation to an attention weighting.",
    "This joint representation is then used to predict the final answer.The GNN-VQA proposed in [128] makes use of a bidirectional GNN that fuses structured and unstructured multi-modal data through a 'supernode'.",
    "After extracting a semantic graph, they use a pretrained sentence BERT model to calculate the similarity between the potential answers and the Visual Genome region descriptions."
  ]
}